node.title: Has Mark Meadows Just Taken Down Donald Trump?
node.description: Former Watergate prosecutor Jill Wine-Banks tells Newsweek how damaging the Mark Meadows revelations could potentially be to former President Donald Trump.

node.title: 2 Pfizer does 70% effective against Omicron hospitalization, data show
node.description: Preliminary analysis of the latest real-world data from South Africa shows that while two shots of the vaccine alone may not stop an infection, it will help avoid serious illness.

node.title: How climate change could impact future tornado disasters
node.description: More than 80 people are confirmed dead after tornadoes ripped through towns in the U.S. As the climate continues to change, experts say future death tolls could be even worse.

node.title: Oil supply is expected to catch up to demand, offering relief on prices.
node.description: The International Energy Agency said that the key factor in its improved outlook was rising production in the United States, Canada and Brazil.
